? a slight error: the best way to deal with a flank attack is to attack in the centre. Better is e5-e4.

? another positional blunder that does not quite give up the game but seriously weakens the squares in front of the castled king. The aim of this move is to play a supported f5-f4 which results in a open g file. However, I am not afraid to open the g file because I see that I can make great use of the file.
